32
00:05:10.061 --> 00:05:12.272
Just take my arm.
at the least.

33
00:05:16.943 --> 00:05:18.945
Was it terribly painful?

34
00:05:20.447 --> 00:05:21.615
Oh. gods.

35
00:05:26.578 --> 00:05:28.788
I took a lance
through the shoulder once.

36
00:05:29.748 --> 00:05:31.708
My deepest sympathies.

37
00:05:31.791 --> 00:05:33.627
The Princess... The Princess...

38
00:05:33.710 --> 00:05:35.670
I am glad I am not a woman.

39
00:05:35.754 --> 00:05:38.381
- My princess...
- My lord...

40
00:05:43.762 --> 00:05:44.763
What is it?

41
00:05:46.014 --> 00:05:47.641
What is it? What is it?

42
00:05:48.266 --> 00:05:49.267
Fuck.

43
00:05:49.976 --> 00:05:52.395
Walk. Walk!

44
00:05:57.567 --> 00:05:59.569
What could she possibly want?

45
00:06:01.446 --> 00:06:03.073
I thought we were past this.

46
00:06:07.786 --> 00:06:10.540
Princess. Ser Laenor.
it is a privilege

47
00:06:10.622 --> 00:06:12.499
to be amongst the first
to congratulate you.

48
00:06:12.582 --> 00:06:14.584
Thank you. Lord Caswell.

49
00:06:14.668 --> 00:06:17.629
If I may be of any service...

50
00:06:17.712 --> 00:06:19.923
The day may yet come. my lord.

51
00:06:27.389 --> 00:06:29.516
We are turning back. all right?

52
00:06:29.599 --> 00:06:32.018
She can come to us. all right?

53
00:06:32.102 --> 00:06:35.105
No. Not unless you wish to carry me down
those fucking stairs.

54
00:06:52.205 --> 00:06:53.957
This is absurd.

55
00:06:54.749 --> 00:06:55.834
Mmm-hmm.

56
00:07:11.308 --> 00:07:12.309
Princess.

57
00:07:30.243 --> 00:07:34.205
Rhaenyra! You should be resting
after your labors.

58
00:07:35.707 --> 00:07:38.460
I have no doubt that
you would prefer that. Your Grace.

59
00:07:38.543 --> 00:07:40.045
You must sit.

60
00:07:40.128 --> 00:07:42.422
Talya. fetch a cushion for the Princess.

61
00:07:42.505 --> 00:07:44.924
- There's no need.
- Nonsense.

62
00:07:45.842 --> 00:07:47.427
We'll finish this later.

63
00:07:48.970 --> 00:07:50.180
Your Grace.

64
00:07:55.810 --> 00:07:58.480
What happy news this morning.

65
00:07:58.563 --> 00:07:59.981
Indeed. Your Grace.

66
00:08:01.024 --> 00:08:02.442
Where is he?

67
00:08:03.276 --> 00:08:06.279
Where is my grandson? There.

68
00:08:07.530 --> 00:08:09.783
There he is.

69
00:08:13.328 --> 00:08:14.954
A fine Prince.

70
00:08:15.580 --> 00:08:16.790
Sturdy.

71
00:08:17.457 --> 00:08:19.876
You will make a fearsome knight.

72
00:08:20.418 --> 00:08:21.920
Yes. you will.

73
00:08:22.003 --> 00:08:23.296
Does the babe have a name yet?

74
00:08:24.339 --> 00:08:25.965
- We haven't spoken...
- Joffrey.

75
00:08:27.050 --> 00:08:28.760
He'll be called Joffrey.

76
00:08:28.843 --> 00:08:30.637
That's an unusual name for a Velaryon.

77
00:08:33.515 --> 00:08:35.725
I do believe he has his father's nose.

78
00:08:37.977 --> 00:08:39.437
Don't you?

79
00:08:44.693 --> 00:08:45.944
If you don't mind. Your Grace.

80
00:08:46.027 --> 00:08:49.406
your daughter has exerted herself
heroically and should rest.

81
00:08:49.489 --> 00:08:50.729
Of course.

82
00:08:52.784 --> 00:08:53.868
There.

83
00:09:00.750 --> 00:09:01.835
Ah!

84
00:09:02.919 --> 00:09:04.546
Well done. my girl.

85
00:09:06.881 --> 00:09:08.883
I do hope the labor was easy.

86
00:09:09.884 --> 00:09:12.470
I think I called the midwife a cunt.

87
00:09:13.096 --> 00:09:14.096
Oh.

88
00:09:20.812 --> 00:09:22.814
Do keep trying. Ser Laenor.

89
00:09:23.773 --> 00:09:26.401
Soon or late. you may get one
who looks like you.

90
00:09:40.665 --> 00:09:44.794
You don't think to consult me
before you name my child?

91
00:09:44.878 --> 00:09:46.880
He's our child. is he not?

92
00:09:48.590 --> 00:09:50.592
Only one of us is bleeding.

93
00:09:50.675 --> 00:09:53.803
I deserve some say in the affairs
of my own family.

94
00:09:54.637 --> 00:09:57.265
You haven't seemed so interested
in our affairs of late.

95
00:10:09.819 --> 00:10:13.239
And he sees a big.
scary dragon!

96
00:10:18.203 --> 00:10:19.204
Mother...

97
00:10:19.913 --> 00:10:21.247
look.

98
00:10:26.461 --> 00:10:27.921
We chose an egg for the baby.

99
00:10:28.213 --> 00:10:29.213
Ah!

100
00:10:29.923 --> 00:10:32.425
That looks like the perfect one.

101
00:10:32.509 --> 00:10:35.303
- I let Luke choose.
- Thank you. Jace.

102
00:10:35.386 --> 00:10:37.764
Not every day an egg
leaves the Dragonpit. Princess.

103
00:10:37.847 --> 00:10:40.391
I thought it best to escort the lads.

104
00:10:42.477 --> 00:10:44.020
Laenor and I thank you. Commander.

105
00:10:45.980 --> 00:10:47.482
Another boy. I heard.

106
00:10:52.904 --> 00:10:55.323
What a fine knight you
are going to make. eh?

107
00:10:55.907 --> 00:10:56.908
Might I?

108
00:10:58.743 --> 00:11:01.538
Ser Harwin wishes to be
introduced to Joffrey.

109
00:11:03.873 --> 00:11:04.874
Of course.

110
00:11:06.793 --> 00:11:08.593
- Joffrey. is it?
- Mmm-hmm.

111
00:11:11.256 --> 00:11:12.256
Hmm.

112
00:11:16.302 --> 00:11:18.596
Father.
please may I hold Joffrey?

113
00:11:18.680 --> 00:11:20.849
- No. no. No.
- Ah-ah-ah.

114
00:11:20.932 --> 00:11:23.142
Back to the Dragonpit for you two.

115
00:11:23.226 --> 00:11:24.352
Come on!

116
00:11:24.435 --> 00:11:26.195
Before they send out
a search party.

117
00:11:37.615 --> 00:11:40.618
You're asleep in front of
the Commander of the City Watch.

118
00:11:42.370 --> 00:11:44.163
Terrible lack of respect.

119
00:11:44.247 --> 00:11:47.333
A certain insolence
runs in the family. I'm afraid.

120
00:12:39.594 --> 00:12:41.238
Call Vermax to heel.
Prince Jacaerys.

121
00:13:17.507 --> 00:13:18.716
Vermax!

122
00:13:19.550 --> 00:13:20.551
Vermax!

123
00:13:24.138 --> 00:13:27.809
<i>Zaldrizo aoho syt aeksio
sagon ao bevilza.</i>

124
00:13:27.892 --> 00:13:29.519
<i>darilaros nuhys...</i>

125
00:13:29.602 --> 00:13:31.997
"You must hold mastery
over your dragon. my young princes."

126
00:13:32.021 --> 00:13:34.691
<i>...hae Darilarot
Aegot Vvsperzomy.</i>

127
00:13:34.774 --> 00:13:36.585
"As Prince Aegon has with Sunfyre."

128
00:13:36.609 --> 00:13:39.612
<i>Zijosy aot tetiri ozlettosy.</i>

129
00:13:39.696 --> 00:13:43.825
<i>toli rybagon zirylo vindilza.</i>

130
00:13:43.908 --> 00:13:45.302
"Once they're fully bound to you.

131
00:13:45.326 --> 00:13:47.578
they will refuse to take instruction
from any other."

132
00:13:51.666 --> 00:13:53.084
- Can I say it?
- Mmm-hmm.

133
00:14:00.633 --> 00:14:02.093
<i>Dracarys.</i> Vermax!

134
00:14:25.116 --> 00:14:27.118
Aemond.
we have a surprise for you.

135
00:14:28.536 --> 00:14:30.580
- What is it?
- Something very special.

136
00:14:32.498 --> 00:14:34.584
You're the only one
of us without a dragon.

137
00:14:34.667 --> 00:14:35.668
Indeed.

138
00:14:35.752 --> 00:14:38.254
And we felt badly about it.

139
00:14:38.337 --> 00:14:41.257
so we found one for you.

140
00:14:41.340 --> 00:14:44.218
A dragon? How?

141
00:14:44.302 --> 00:14:45.636
The gods provide.

142
00:14:54.395 --> 00:14:57.106
- Behold...
- The Pink Dread!

143
00:15:00.068 --> 00:15:01.402
Be sure to mount her carefully.

144
00:15:01.486 --> 00:15:02.987
First flight's always rough.

145
00:16:40.042 --> 00:16:41.544
This one has 60 rings...

146
00:16:42.837 --> 00:16:44.422
and two pairs of legs on each.

147
00:16:45.506 --> 00:16:46.799
That's 240.

148
00:16:48.301 --> 00:16:49.302
Yes. it is.

149
00:16:52.096 --> 00:16:53.181
It has eyes...

150
00:16:54.557 --> 00:16:55.558
though...

151
00:16:56.309 --> 00:16:57.602
I don't believe it can see.

152
00:16:59.312 --> 00:17:01.189
And why is that so. do you think?

153
00:17:03.566 --> 00:17:05.067
It is beyond our understanding.

154
00:17:07.612 --> 00:17:10.239
I suppose you're right.
Some things just are.

155
00:17:14.368 --> 00:17:15.368
Your Grace.

156
00:17:17.079 --> 00:17:18.080
Aemond.

157
00:17:19.123 --> 00:17:20.833
- What have you done?
- He did it again.

158
00:17:20.917 --> 00:17:22.227
After how many times
you've been warned.

159
00:17:22.251 --> 00:17:23.604
must I have you confined
to your chambers?

160
00:17:23.628 --> 00:17:25.522
- They made me do it!
- As if you needed encouragement.

161
00:17:25.546 --> 00:17:27.441
Your obsession with those beasts
goes beyond understanding.

162
00:17:27.465 --> 00:17:29.133
They gave me a pig!

163
00:17:29.926 --> 00:17:30.927
A what?

164
00:17:31.010 --> 00:17:32.595
They said they found a dragon for me.

165
00:17:32.678 --> 00:17:34.889
The last ring has no legs at all.

166
00:17:34.972 --> 00:17:36.349
But it was a pig.

167
00:17:36.933 --> 00:17:38.976
You will have a dragon one day.

168
00:17:39.685 --> 00:17:41.938
- He'll have to close an eye.
- I know it.

169
00:17:43.981 --> 00:17:45.107
They all laughed.

170
00:17:49.278 --> 00:17:52.323
They made wings for it.
apparently. and a tail.

171
00:17:52.406 --> 00:17:54.134
The lad shouldn't
have been so credulous.

172
00:17:54.158 --> 00:17:55.201
He's a child.

173
00:17:55.284 --> 00:17:58.412
He thought they'd happened
upon some wild unnamed dragon

174
00:17:58.496 --> 00:17:59.872
and lured it to the Dragonpit?

175
00:17:59.956 --> 00:18:01.499
Your grandsons are a menace.

176
00:18:01.582 --> 00:18:03.292
They're more children than he is.

177
00:18:03.376 --> 00:18:06.087
They're savages.
Though it's not surprising.

178
00:18:08.589 --> 00:18:11.550
Are you sure it wasn't
our Aegon who put them up to it?

179
00:18:15.471 --> 00:18:17.348
It's a wonder to me
their eggs ever hatched.

180
00:18:18.933 --> 00:18:20.977
- And why is that?
- You know why.

181
00:18:21.060 --> 00:18:22.895
- I'm afraid I don't.
- Don't...

182
00:18:24.605 --> 00:18:25.815
Viserys...

183
00:18:28.276 --> 00:18:30.278
We shall continue
this afternoon. Eddard.

184
00:18:38.953 --> 00:18:41.539
I have raised this matter before

185
00:18:41.622 --> 00:18:44.125
and you forbade me to speak of it.
so I held my tongue.

186
00:18:45.960 --> 00:18:48.671
To have one child
like that is a mistake.

187
00:18:48.754 --> 00:18:51.257
to have three is an insult.

188
00:18:51.340 --> 00:18:54.176
to the throne. to you.
to House Velaryon

189
00:18:54.260 --> 00:18:56.304
and the match you battled
so hard to make for her.

190
00:18:56.387 --> 00:18:58.848
Not to mention decency itself.

191
00:19:00.141 --> 00:19:02.143
I had a black mare once.

192
00:19:02.977 --> 00:19:04.687
Black like a raven.

193
00:19:04.770 --> 00:19:07.523
One day. she escaped her pasture

194
00:19:07.606 --> 00:19:10.443
and the neighboring stallion
sired a foal on her.

195
00:19:12.486 --> 00:19:16.657
The stallion was as silver as the moon
on a winter's night

196
00:19:16.741 --> 00:19:19.410
and the foal. when it was born.

197
00:19:19.493 --> 00:19:21.454
chestnut.

198
00:19:22.246 --> 00:19:26.167
Just the most unremarkable
brown horse you ever saw.

199
00:19:28.252 --> 00:19:30.629
Nature is a thing of mysterious works.

200
00:19:37.094 --> 00:19:38.387
How do you know?

201
00:19:40.306 --> 00:19:41.932
The silver stallion.

202
00:19:42.558 --> 00:19:43.934
How do you know it was him?

203
00:19:45.853 --> 00:19:47.688
Did you witness the act itself?

204
00:19:51.859 --> 00:19:54.028
The consequences

205
00:19:54.111 --> 00:19:57.031
of an allegation like the one you toy at

206
00:19:57.114 --> 00:19:58.449
would be dire.

207
00:20:07.124 --> 00:20:08.876
Do not speak of this again.

208
00:20:19.804 --> 00:20:22.098
<i>Have I lost my sanity.
Ser Criston?</i>

209
00:20:22.181 --> 00:20:23.307
Do my senses lead me astray?

210
00:20:23.391 --> 00:20:26.143
Or is everyone else asleep.
dreaming the same woolly dream?

211
00:20:26.227 --> 00:20:28.229
Sometimes seems so. Your Grace.

212
00:20:30.731 --> 00:20:33.067
She flaunts the privilege
of her inheritance without shame.

213
00:20:33.150 --> 00:20:35.128
She expects everyone in the Red Keep
to deny the truth

214
00:20:35.152 --> 00:20:36.487
our eyes can all plainly see.

215
00:20:36.570 --> 00:20:37.964
- And the King. her father...
- He knows.

216
00:20:37.988 --> 00:20:39.073
Of course. he knows.

217
00:20:39.156 --> 00:20:40.759
Or did once. but has convinced
himself otherwise.

218
00:20:40.783 --> 00:20:42.785
He'll do naught
but make excuses for her.

219
00:20:43.577 --> 00:20:47.206
The Princess Rhaenyra
is brazen and relentless.

220
00:20:47.289 --> 00:20:50.709
A spider who stings
and sucks her prey dry.

221
00:20:51.419 --> 00:20:53.421
A spoiled cunt.

222
00:20:58.759 --> 00:21:01.387
That was beneath me. Your Grace.
I apologize.

223
00:21:04.557 --> 00:21:06.350
I have to believe.

224
00:21:06.434 --> 00:21:10.062
that in the end.
honor and decency will prevail.

225
00:21:11.147 --> 00:21:14.358
We need to hew to that
and to each other.

226
00:21:33.252 --> 00:21:34.420
Whose idea was it?

227
00:21:39.925 --> 00:21:41.510
The pig.

228
00:21:41.594 --> 00:21:44.221
- Was it your plot?
- No...

229
00:21:44.847 --> 00:21:47.850
It was Jace and...

230
00:21:49.143 --> 00:21:51.270
it was the two of them.

231
00:21:51.353 --> 00:21:52.688
I couldn't be sure.

232
00:21:52.771 --> 00:21:54.190
Aemond is your brother.

233
00:21:54.273 --> 00:21:56.400
- Well. he's a twat.
- We are family.

234
00:21:56.484 --> 00:21:58.819
You may cuff him about
as you wish at home.

235
00:21:58.903 --> 00:22:02.031
but in the world.
we must defend our own.

236
00:22:02.114 --> 00:22:03.199
It was funny.

237
00:22:03.282 --> 00:22:06.118
Do you think Rhaenyra's sons
will be your playthings forever?

238
00:22:07.870 --> 00:22:08.871
As things stand...

239
00:22:09.955 --> 00:22:13.584
Rhaenyra will ascend the throne
and Jacaerys Targaryen will be her heir.

240
00:22:14.168 --> 00:22:16.754
- So?
- You are nearly a man-grown.

241
00:22:16.837 --> 00:22:18.923
How is it that
you can be so shortsighted?

242
00:22:21.675 --> 00:22:23.677
If Rhaenyra comes into power...

243
00:22:24.303 --> 00:22:26.931
your very life could be forfeit.

244
00:22:28.015 --> 00:22:29.433
Aemond's as well.

245
00:22:30.434 --> 00:22:33.312
She could move to cut off any challenge
to her succession.

246
00:22:34.063 --> 00:22:35.916
- Then I won't challenge...
- You are the challenge!

247
00:22:35.940 --> 00:22:37.441
You are the challenge. Aegon!

248
00:22:37.525 --> 00:22:40.152
Simply by living and breathing!

249
00:22:44.573 --> 00:22:47.535
You are the King's firstborn son

250
00:22:47.618 --> 00:22:50.412
and what they know.
what everyone in the realm knows

251
00:22:50.496 --> 00:22:52.498
in their blood and in their bones...

252
00:22:53.666 --> 00:22:56.669
is that one day. you will be our King.

253
00:23:05.594 --> 00:23:06.637
Get dressed.

254
00:24:02.318 --> 00:24:03.986
<i>Dracarys!</i>

255
00:24:31.805 --> 00:24:34.224
The lamb hearts are excellent.

256
00:24:34.308 --> 00:24:37.061
We are fortunate in our cook.
Your Excellence.

257
00:24:37.144 --> 00:24:38.538
There's a plum-cake
yet to be served.

258
00:24:38.562 --> 00:24:40.282
which will have us
fighting over the crumbs.

259
00:24:40.564 --> 00:24:42.566
Then before we come to blows...

260
00:24:44.109 --> 00:24:47.988
a toast to Aegon the Conqueror.
your exalted forebear.

261
00:24:48.072 --> 00:24:51.659
who joined our cause against Volantis
in the Century of Blood.

262
00:24:51.742 --> 00:24:55.287
On the great dragon Balerion.
he flew to our aid in Lys

263
00:24:55.371 --> 00:24:58.957
and burned a fleet of enemy ships.
thus turning the tide.

264
00:25:01.168 --> 00:25:03.796
- Aegon the Conqueror.
- To Aegon.

265
00:25:07.007 --> 00:25:08.887
This brings me to some business.

266
00:25:09.635 --> 00:25:11.804
A proposal I wish to make

267
00:25:11.887 --> 00:25:14.807
in the spirit of honoring
our storied alliance.

268
00:25:14.890 --> 00:25:17.351
If your aim is to marry
one of our daughters. Your Excellence.

269
00:25:17.434 --> 00:25:19.537
you might have said so
and spared us the history lesson.

270
00:25:19.561 --> 00:25:20.881
What?

271
00:25:21.855 --> 00:25:25.025
I would not count myself
so deserving. my lady Laena.

272
00:25:27.653 --> 00:25:32.032
I wish to offer you
a permanent residence here in Pentos.

273
00:25:32.116 --> 00:25:34.535
This manse I would gift
to you. outright.

274
00:25:34.618 --> 00:25:36.912
along with its farms and lands.

275
00:25:36.995 --> 00:25:38.706
the vineyard and the wood.

276
00:25:38.789 --> 00:25:40.916
The tenants would pay
their tributes annually

277
00:25:40.999 --> 00:25:42.876
to their new Targaryen lord.

278
00:25:42.960 --> 00:25:45.713
You would have your freedom
of the city and the harbor.

279
00:25:45.796 --> 00:25:48.590
as befits your royal station.

280
00:25:51.760 --> 00:25:53.137
Continue.

281
00:25:53.220 --> 00:25:56.515
Lys and its allies rise again.

282
00:25:56.598 --> 00:26:00.728
The Triarchy has made common cause
with Qoren Martell of Dorne.

283
00:26:01.228 --> 00:26:04.273
At any moment.
they may turn their sights north.

284
00:26:04.356 --> 00:26:06.775
Your family has dragons.

285
00:26:06.859 --> 00:26:10.696
Three now. mayhaps four in the future.

286
00:26:11.697 --> 00:26:15.534
My aim is to protect Pentos
from the lustful eye of the Triarchy.

287
00:26:15.617 --> 00:26:19.329
Aid Pentos in this. as Aegon once did...

288
00:26:19.955 --> 00:26:24.126
and my gratitude will fill your cup
and overflow it.

289
00:26:24.209 --> 00:26:26.503
Your Excellence. we are travelers.

290
00:26:26.587 --> 00:26:29.214
We've already extended our visit here.

291
00:26:33.594 --> 00:26:35.387
It's a most generous offer.

292
00:26:36.054 --> 00:26:38.056
And one we will certainly entertain.

293
00:27:08.545 --> 00:27:11.089
You are considering
Prince Reggio's offer.

294
00:27:11.173 --> 00:27:13.175
We have a good life here.

295
00:27:13.258 --> 00:27:16.553
We're free to do as we please.
welcomed and feted.

296
00:27:16.637 --> 00:27:19.056
- And eternally guests.
- Precisely.

297
00:27:19.139 --> 00:27:22.100
We are without responsibility.
The political scheming.

298
00:27:22.184 --> 00:27:24.853
the endless shifting
of loyalties and succession

299
00:27:24.937 --> 00:27:26.438
is none of ours.

300
00:27:27.189 --> 00:27:30.192
- They are using us.
- It's refreshing. isn't it?

301
00:27:31.652 --> 00:27:33.362
A simple transaction.

302
00:27:33.445 --> 00:27:35.948
We have dragons. they have gold.

303
00:27:41.161 --> 00:27:43.038
We are more than this. Daemon.

304
00:27:43.121 --> 00:27:44.456
We are not minstrels or mummers

305
00:27:44.540 --> 00:27:46.184
who play at the pleasure
of an alien prince.

306
00:27:46.208 --> 00:27:48.627
We are the blood of Old Valyria.

307
00:27:49.628 --> 00:27:50.963
We don't belong here.

308
00:27:51.046 --> 00:27:53.465
Valyria is gone.
We don't belong anywhere.

309
00:27:59.596 --> 00:28:04.184
I want my child to be born
where I was born. on Driftmark.

310
00:28:04.268 --> 00:28:05.435
in my lord father's castle.

311
00:28:05.519 --> 00:28:08.230
I want my daughters to be
raised in their homeland

312
00:28:08.313 --> 00:28:12.317
with their family
according to their birthright.

313
00:28:14.444 --> 00:28:17.906
And at my end. I want to die
a dragonrider's death.

314
00:28:17.990 --> 00:28:20.617
Not that of some fat country lord.

315
00:28:53.609 --> 00:28:55.777
Soften your knees.

316
00:28:55.861 --> 00:28:56.862
Feet light.

317
00:28:58.280 --> 00:29:00.008
Keep your feet light
and your hands heavy.

318
00:29:00.032 --> 00:29:02.576
This is the stuff. Lyonel.

319
00:29:02.659 --> 00:29:06.079
Lads that learn together.
train together...

320
00:29:06.163 --> 00:29:09.041
knock each other down.
pick each other up.

321
00:29:09.124 --> 00:29:11.877
They will certainly form
a lifelong bond. wouldn't you agree?

322
00:29:12.628 --> 00:29:14.087
That is the hope. Your Grace.

323
00:29:16.965 --> 00:29:19.551
Don't stand too upright. my prince.
You'll get knocked down.

324
00:29:30.729 --> 00:29:31.730
Aegon.

325
00:29:33.523 --> 00:29:35.293
I've won my first bout.
Ser Criston.

326
00:29:35.317 --> 00:29:37.736
My opponent sues for mercy.

327
00:29:38.278 --> 00:29:41.406
You'll have a new opponent then.
my Lord of the Straw.

328
00:29:41.490 --> 00:29:43.075
Let's see if you can touch me.

329
00:29:44.034 --> 00:29:45.452
You and your brother.

330
00:30:13.021 --> 00:30:14.648
You're gonna have
to do better than that.

331
00:30:19.111 --> 00:30:20.278
Ah!

332
00:30:20.362 --> 00:30:21.363
Weapons up. boys.

333
00:30:21.947 --> 00:30:23.573
Give your enemies no quarter.

334
00:30:25.909 --> 00:30:27.619
It seems the younger boys
could do better

335
00:30:27.703 --> 00:30:30.998
with a bit of your attention.
Ser Criston.

336
00:30:31.081 --> 00:30:34.001
You question my method
of instruction. ser?

337
00:30:34.084 --> 00:30:37.546
Oh. I merely suggest that
method be applied to all your pupils.

338
00:30:41.258 --> 00:30:42.259
Very well.

339
00:30:45.846 --> 00:30:47.848
Jacaerys. come here.

340
00:30:47.931 --> 00:30:49.141
You spar with Aegon.

341
00:30:52.352 --> 00:30:53.770
Eldest son against eldest son.

342
00:30:57.024 --> 00:30:58.358
It's hardly a fair match.

343
00:30:58.442 --> 00:31:00.670
I know you've never seen true battle.
ser. but when steel is drawn.

344
00:31:00.694 --> 00:31:02.654
a fair match isn't something
anyone should expect.

345
00:31:05.407 --> 00:31:06.616
Blades up.

346
00:31:07.868 --> 00:31:08.952
Engage.

347
00:31:14.875 --> 00:31:15.875
Ah!

348
00:31:33.351 --> 00:31:34.811
- Foul play.
- I'll deal with him.

349
00:31:37.898 --> 00:31:39.733
Plant your feet.
You have a height advantage.

350
00:31:39.816 --> 00:31:42.611
Use it. Advance on him...

351
00:31:46.990 --> 00:31:48.116
You!

352
00:31:49.618 --> 00:31:50.786
Close with him.

353
00:31:51.661 --> 00:31:53.914
Press him backward!
Close with him!

354
00:31:54.414 --> 00:31:56.416
Stay on the attack!
Use your feet!

355
00:31:59.753 --> 00:32:00.754
Don't let him get up.

356
00:32:03.340 --> 00:32:04.591
Stay on the attack!

357
00:32:05.967 --> 00:32:07.177
Enough!

358
00:32:08.929 --> 00:32:11.556
- You dare put hands on me?
- Aegon!

359
00:32:11.640 --> 00:32:13.520
You forget yourself. Strong.
That is the Prince.

360
00:32:13.600 --> 00:32:15.227
This is what you teach. Cole?

361
00:32:17.771 --> 00:32:18.980
Cruelty...

362
00:32:19.981 --> 00:32:21.149
to the weaker opponent?

363
00:32:24.152 --> 00:32:25.922
Your interest
in the princeling's training

364
00:32:25.946 --> 00:32:27.364
is quite unusual. Commander.

365
00:32:29.658 --> 00:32:31.493
Most men would only
have that kind of devotion

366
00:32:31.576 --> 00:32:32.994
toward a cousin...

367
00:32:34.746 --> 00:32:35.747
or a brother...

368
00:32:36.832 --> 00:32:37.833
or a son.

369
00:32:54.474 --> 00:32:56.101
Get back!

370
00:32:56.643 --> 00:32:58.103
Say it again!

371
00:32:58.937 --> 00:33:00.355
Say it again!

372
00:33:00.438 --> 00:33:02.190
Thought as much.

373
00:33:05.652 --> 00:33:07.292
Let him be bathed
with a cloth.

374
00:33:07.320 --> 00:33:08.905
and see to it the cook

375
00:33:08.989 --> 00:33:10.991
gives you a good. clear wine to drink.

376
00:33:13.493 --> 00:33:14.578
Princess...

377
00:33:15.412 --> 00:33:18.623
there's been an incident in the yard.

378
00:33:28.008 --> 00:33:30.260
It fills me
with unrelenting shame.

379
00:33:30.343 --> 00:33:32.679
So that's what
this is about then?

380
00:33:32.762 --> 00:33:35.390
- Your shame?
- Our shame. Harwin!

381
00:33:36.349 --> 00:33:37.893
Shame on the whole of House Strong.

382
00:33:37.976 --> 00:33:40.854
Because I laid my hands
on that insufferable Cole.

383
00:33:40.937 --> 00:33:41.937
the son of a steward?

384
00:33:41.938 --> 00:33:43.374
He is a Knight
of the Kingsguard now.

385
00:33:43.398 --> 00:33:45.293
- a defender of the crown.
- He assailed Prince Jacaerys.

386
00:33:45.317 --> 00:33:47.152
the future heir to the throne.

387
00:33:49.196 --> 00:33:53.366
You have laid us open to accusations

388
00:33:53.450 --> 00:33:55.202
of an uglier treachery.

389
00:33:55.285 --> 00:33:57.454
And what treachery is that?

390
00:33:59.956 --> 00:34:02.167
Don't play the fool with me. boy.

391
00:34:03.710 --> 00:34:06.880
Your intimacy with the Princess Rhaenyra

392
00:34:06.963 --> 00:34:09.925
is an offense that would
mean exile and death...

393
00:34:10.467 --> 00:34:14.095
for you. for her. for the children!

394
00:34:15.180 --> 00:34:17.349
It is rumor only...

395
00:34:19.476 --> 00:34:20.852
spun by the Princess's rivals.

396
00:34:20.936 --> 00:34:22.520
People have eyes. boy.

397
00:34:25.398 --> 00:34:29.694
Yet His Grace the King. it seems.
will not accept what his eyes see.

398
00:34:29.778 --> 00:34:34.366
This flimsy shield alone
stands between you and the headsman.

399
00:34:35.492 --> 00:34:38.536
The willful blindness of a father
towards his child.

400
00:34:38.620 --> 00:34:41.081
I wish my father affected
a similar blindness.

401
00:34:41.164 --> 00:34:43.458
Have I not these many years?

402
00:34:44.084 --> 00:34:46.253
And yet today. you publicly assaulted

403
00:34:46.336 --> 00:34:49.339
a knight of the Kingsguard
in the... in the defense of your...

404
00:34:52.175 --> 00:34:55.387
You have your honor
and I have mine.

405
00:35:03.520 --> 00:35:05.522
To ease the pain. Princess.

406
00:35:17.909 --> 00:35:20.578
- Thank you.
- You'll feel better in a day or two.

407
00:35:20.662 --> 00:35:22.289
when the milk dries up.

408
00:35:40.890 --> 00:35:42.892
My dear wife.

409
00:35:42.976 --> 00:35:44.811
Princess.

410
00:35:44.894 --> 00:35:45.894
Oh.

411
00:35:46.646 --> 00:35:47.856
I fell down.

412
00:35:50.108 --> 00:35:52.277
- Where have you been?
- Out with Qarl.

413
00:35:52.360 --> 00:35:53.360
Didn't I mention it?

414
00:35:55.238 --> 00:35:57.532
Are you in very much pain?

415
00:35:57.615 --> 00:35:58.616
The milk...

416
00:35:59.868 --> 00:36:02.120
- swells the breasts...
- Would you mind. Ser Qarl?

417
00:36:02.203 --> 00:36:03.788
I would like to speak with my husband.

418
00:36:03.872 --> 00:36:05.582
Of course. Princess.

419
00:36:17.052 --> 00:36:21.181
War is afoot again
in the Stepstones. Rhaenyra.

420
00:36:22.015 --> 00:36:26.478
The Triarchy takes new life
from its alliance with Dorne.

421
00:36:27.562 --> 00:36:29.564
They're waylaying ships and cargo.

422
00:36:30.190 --> 00:36:32.859
Qarl's been fighting there.
He showed me a...

423
00:36:36.112 --> 00:36:39.908
He showed me a sack of sapphires
big as walnuts

424
00:36:39.991 --> 00:36:41.993
he took from the pirate he slew.

425
00:36:42.827 --> 00:36:43.912
Ah...

426
00:36:44.537 --> 00:36:47.832
After all this time.
this is just what I need.

427
00:36:47.916 --> 00:36:49.584
a little adventure.

428
00:36:49.667 --> 00:36:53.088
A good. honest battle
to enliven my blood again.

429
00:36:54.381 --> 00:36:56.966
He says there is
a Tyroshi general there.

430
00:36:57.050 --> 00:36:58.802
a giant. they say.

431
00:36:58.885 --> 00:37:03.515
who dyes his beard purple
and wears women's frocks.

432
00:37:07.352 --> 00:37:09.312
A few months. maybe...

433
00:37:09.396 --> 00:37:10.396
Hmm?

434
00:37:13.983 --> 00:37:15.944
To be back at sea.

435
00:37:17.904 --> 00:37:19.823
Are you mad?

436
00:37:20.740 --> 00:37:22.158
Do you know what's happened...

437
00:37:23.451 --> 00:37:25.554
while you've been guzzling all the ale
in Flea Bottom?

438
00:37:25.578 --> 00:37:27.205
Gods know what besides?

439
00:37:28.248 --> 00:37:30.542
Dark rumors are hunting us. Laenor.

440
00:37:30.625 --> 00:37:32.710
They nip at our heels.

441
00:37:32.794 --> 00:37:37.674
Questions about our sons' parentage.

442
00:37:38.591 --> 00:37:40.885
Vile. disgusting insinuations.

443
00:37:41.970 --> 00:37:43.596
Insinuations. are they?

444
00:37:44.097 --> 00:37:46.057
They are our sons!

445
00:37:46.141 --> 00:37:48.143
Yours and mine.

446
00:37:49.018 --> 00:37:51.229
And their true father
will not abandon them now

447
00:37:51.312 --> 00:37:54.732
to go carousing through the Narrow Sea.
waggling his sword

448
00:37:54.816 --> 00:37:57.193
- and winking at his sailors.
- I am a knight...

449
00:37:59.529 --> 00:38:00.530
and a warrior.

450
00:38:01.781 --> 00:38:06.744
And I have played
my part here. faithfully...

451
00:38:07.996 --> 00:38:10.999
for ten years.

452
00:38:12.167 --> 00:38:15.003
- I am owed some...
- You are owed nothing!

453
00:38:16.212 --> 00:38:21.176
For ten years. you have indulged
yourself at court.

454
00:38:21.259 --> 00:38:23.720
bought the finest horses.

455
00:38:23.803 --> 00:38:26.222
drunk the rarest of wines.

456
00:38:26.306 --> 00:38:27.932
fucked the lustiest boys.

457
00:38:28.016 --> 00:38:31.436
This was our agreement.
I have not begrudged you.

458
00:38:32.312 --> 00:38:33.396
But...

459
00:38:35.064 --> 00:38:39.319
you do not desert your post
when the storm lashes.

460
00:38:39.402 --> 00:38:44.032
The wise sailor
flees the storm as it gathers.

461
00:38:54.417 --> 00:38:56.669
Very well then.
I command you.

462
00:38:58.129 --> 00:39:00.048
As your Princess
and the heir to the throne.

463
00:39:00.131 --> 00:39:02.217
you are commanded

464
00:39:02.300 --> 00:39:05.678
to remain in King's Landing
and at my side.

465
00:39:26.282 --> 00:39:28.284
It's been eight years. sweetling.

466
00:39:29.827 --> 00:39:32.747
- Half of them never do. you know?
- What?

467
00:39:35.708 --> 00:39:36.709
Hatch.

468
00:39:39.796 --> 00:39:41.422
Will they let me stay?

469
00:39:42.757 --> 00:39:44.384
Will who let you stay?

470
00:39:44.926 --> 00:39:46.553
The Prince of Pentos.

471
00:39:47.637 --> 00:39:49.264
I don't understand.

472
00:39:50.390 --> 00:39:52.392
He wants you and father...

473
00:39:53.768 --> 00:39:55.186
and Baela...

474
00:39:55.770 --> 00:39:57.605
'cause you have dragons.

475
00:40:02.068 --> 00:40:05.738
There is more than one way
to bind yourself to a dragon.

476
00:40:05.822 --> 00:40:10.451
I was without one
until I was 15 years old

477
00:40:10.535 --> 00:40:14.747
and now I ride Vhagar.
the largest in the world.

478
00:40:18.084 --> 00:40:19.919
You have a harder road.

479
00:40:20.003 --> 00:40:21.963
Baela's dragon was born to her.

480
00:40:24.507 --> 00:40:26.050
But if you wish to be a rider.

481
00:40:26.134 --> 00:40:29.137
you must claim that right.

482
00:40:30.763 --> 00:40:32.765
Your father would tell you the same.

483
00:40:34.267 --> 00:40:35.643
Father ignores me.

484
00:40:42.609 --> 00:40:44.110
He's doing his best.

485
00:41:22.273 --> 00:41:24.275
Laenor has written.

486
00:41:25.652 --> 00:41:27.820
Rhaenyra has delivered another son.

487
00:41:30.239 --> 00:41:31.824
Does your brother mention if this one

488
00:41:31.908 --> 00:41:34.452
also bears a marked
but entirely coincidental

489
00:41:34.535 --> 00:41:37.163
resemblance to the Commander
of the City Watch?

490
00:41:38.331 --> 00:41:40.625
He seems to have left that detail out.

491
00:41:40.708 --> 00:41:41.709
Mmm.

492
00:41:43.586 --> 00:41:45.713
I miss my brother. Daemon.

493
00:41:48.216 --> 00:41:49.467
As I think do you.

494
00:41:51.594 --> 00:41:53.805
I miss Westerosi strongwine.

495
00:41:55.515 --> 00:41:58.226
It could be depended on for a few hours
of peaceful oblivion.

496
00:42:00.353 --> 00:42:02.772
This amber shit that they drink here.

497
00:42:10.571 --> 00:42:12.615
Do you never long for home?

498
00:42:12.699 --> 00:42:14.117
No.

499
00:42:14.200 --> 00:42:16.786
- I don't believe you.
- Believe what you please.

500
00:42:16.869 --> 00:42:20.957
You laud the virtues of Pentos.
but you have no interest in it.

501
00:42:21.040 --> 00:42:23.626
If you did. you would venture
into the city. but instead.

502
00:42:23.710 --> 00:42:27.171
you spend your time here.
in the library. reading accounts

503
00:42:27.255 --> 00:42:30.550
of the same dead dragonlords
whose legacy you claim

504
00:42:30.633 --> 00:42:32.093
has no hold on you.

505
00:42:32.176 --> 00:42:34.637
Didn't know I was being
so minutely observed.

506
00:42:34.721 --> 00:42:36.180
You do not sleep.

507
00:42:36.264 --> 00:42:38.808
Well. how can I with you
haunting my every move?

508
00:42:42.228 --> 00:42:44.668
Life has. I know. disappointed you.

509
00:42:45.523 --> 00:42:48.151
Perhaps. I too. am not the wife
you would've wished for yourself.

510
00:42:48.234 --> 00:42:49.444
Laena.

511
00:42:49.527 --> 00:42:50.987
It does not pain me.

512
00:42:52.321 --> 00:42:53.865
I have made my peace.

513
00:42:58.161 --> 00:42:59.787
But you are more than this. Daemon.

514
00:43:02.248 --> 00:43:05.209
The man I married was more than this.

515
00:43:12.967 --> 00:43:15.303
It is Lord Blackwood's
contention. therefore.

516
00:43:15.386 --> 00:43:17.066
that the Brackens moved
the boundary stones

517
00:43:17.096 --> 00:43:18.431
in the dead of the night

518
00:43:18.514 --> 00:43:20.975
and put their horses
to graze in his field.

519
00:43:21.058 --> 00:43:23.603
Why was this issue not
brought before Lord Grover?

520
00:43:23.686 --> 00:43:26.814
Has he grown so feeble
he cannot settle a quarrel over rocks?

521
00:43:26.898 --> 00:43:31.277
I've heard tale that Lord Grover's son
now rules Riverrun in all but name.

522
00:43:31.360 --> 00:43:35.656
Well. he is also a Tully
and this remains a Tully problem.

523
00:43:35.740 --> 00:43:36.908
I would agree.

524
00:43:37.950 --> 00:43:40.369
- If we may move on. my lords...
- And yet.

525
00:43:40.453 --> 00:43:41.913
the Brackens and the Blackwoods

526
00:43:41.996 --> 00:43:44.040
will use any excuse
to spill each other's blood.

527
00:43:47.293 --> 00:43:50.588
So this dispute bears looking into.

528
00:43:50.671 --> 00:43:52.089
There will be countryfolk who know

529
00:43:52.173 --> 00:43:54.550
where the lines have
been drawn for generations.

530
00:43:54.634 --> 00:43:55.927
That is easy enough.

531
00:43:57.094 --> 00:43:58.554
Of course.

532
00:44:00.807 --> 00:44:01.933
Ser Tyland.

533
00:44:03.059 --> 00:44:05.436
Um. we should address

534
00:44:05.520 --> 00:44:08.397
the latest developments
in the Stepstones. my lords.

535
00:44:08.481 --> 00:44:11.108
Will we ever be shut
of that blasted place?

536
00:44:11.192 --> 00:44:12.985
If you ask me.
I think the Blackwoods have

537
00:44:13.069 --> 00:44:14.570
- the upper hand.
- No.

538
00:44:14.654 --> 00:44:17.031
We've moved on to the Stepstones.
Lord Beesbury.

539
00:44:17.114 --> 00:44:20.576
And the Triarchy's
new alliance with Dorne.

540
00:44:20.660 --> 00:44:22.995
I was hoping
our negotiations with Sunspear

541
00:44:23.079 --> 00:44:24.580
might persuade
them to see reason.

542
00:44:26.499 --> 00:44:29.377
To trust a Martell
is to be disappointed.

543
00:44:29.460 --> 00:44:31.963
And where. I wonder.
is our Prince Daemon?

544
00:44:32.046 --> 00:44:34.507
Or I suppose I should call him King.
as he styled himself

545
00:44:34.590 --> 00:44:37.218
when he won a battle there... once.

546
00:44:37.301 --> 00:44:40.054
That was a decade ago and he has
since left the region undefended.

547
00:44:40.137 --> 00:44:41.907
We have left it undefended.

548
00:44:41.931 --> 00:44:44.892
There should've been
fortifications built.

549
00:44:44.976 --> 00:44:46.811
watchtowers. a fleet of ships.

550
00:44:46.894 --> 00:44:49.605
a garrison of soldiers
sent to hold our ground.

551
00:44:49.689 --> 00:44:50.898
We cannot afford it.

552
00:44:53.150 --> 00:44:56.487
Our coffers are great. but not infinite.

553
00:44:57.154 --> 00:44:59.156
We must consider
the cost to our subjects.

554
00:44:59.240 --> 00:45:02.243
- I must agree.
- The cost of war is greater.

555
00:45:04.620 --> 00:45:08.833
But we have been lax
and the old monster now lifts its head.

556
00:45:14.088 --> 00:45:15.256
Let us be finished.

557
00:45:16.841 --> 00:45:18.259
Yes.

558
00:45:22.305 --> 00:45:23.306
Wait.

559
00:45:24.348 --> 00:45:25.474
I wish to speak.

560
00:45:27.226 --> 00:45:28.227
Be seated.

561
00:45:37.695 --> 00:45:40.656
I have felt the...

562
00:45:41.824 --> 00:45:43.117
strife...

563
00:45:44.076 --> 00:45:46.454
between our families of late. my queen.

564
00:45:49.123 --> 00:45:52.960
And for any offense given by mine.
I apologize.

565
00:45:55.046 --> 00:45:57.256
But we are one house.

566
00:45:58.299 --> 00:46:00.801
And long before that.

567
00:46:00.885 --> 00:46:02.303
we were friends.

568
00:46:08.434 --> 00:46:11.187
My son Jacaerys will inherit
the Iron Throne after me.

569
00:46:11.270 --> 00:46:13.940
I propose we betroth him
to your daughter. Helaena.

570
00:46:15.816 --> 00:46:17.818
Ally ourselves...

571
00:46:18.444 --> 00:46:20.321
once and for all.

572
00:46:20.905 --> 00:46:22.615
Let them rule together.

573
00:46:22.698 --> 00:46:24.700
A most judicious proposition.

574
00:46:29.747 --> 00:46:33.292
Additionally. if Syrax brings forth
another clutch of eggs.

575
00:46:33.376 --> 00:46:35.836
your son Aemond will have
his choice of them. uh...

576
00:46:37.088 --> 00:46:39.715
a symbol of our goodwill.

577
00:46:42.718 --> 00:46:44.095
Rhaenyra...

578
00:46:51.936 --> 00:46:54.563
Oh. Seven Hells. Um...

579
00:46:56.816 --> 00:46:58.442
My dear...

580
00:46:58.526 --> 00:47:00.945
a dragon's egg is a handsome gift.

581
00:47:02.571 --> 00:47:06.158
The King and I thank you for your offer
and we will consider it duly.

582
00:47:06.242 --> 00:47:08.244
You must rest now. husband.

583
00:47:11.455 --> 00:47:12.832
Yes.

584
00:47:19.171 --> 00:47:22.967
<i>How sweetly the fox speaks
when it's been cornered by the hounds.</i>

585
00:47:23.050 --> 00:47:26.095
- She is sincere.
- She is desperate.

586
00:47:26.178 --> 00:47:28.389
She feels the earth
washing away beneath her feet

587
00:47:28.472 --> 00:47:30.808
and now she expects us
to ignore her transgressions

588
00:47:30.891 --> 00:47:34.145
and for me to marry my only daughter
to one of her...

589
00:47:34.228 --> 00:47:35.980
plain-featured sons.

590
00:47:36.063 --> 00:47:38.691
The proposal is a good one. my queen.

591
00:47:39.734 --> 00:47:41.318
We're a family.

592
00:47:41.402 --> 00:47:43.738
Let us put aside
these childish quarrels.

593
00:47:43.821 --> 00:47:46.240
Join hands and be stronger for it.

594
00:47:47.366 --> 00:47:49.368
You may do as you wish. husband...

595
00:47:50.369 --> 00:47:52.788
when I am cold in my grave.

596
00:47:53.539 --> 00:47:54.540
Alicent.

597
00:47:56.584 --> 00:47:57.668
Alicent!

598
00:48:21.275 --> 00:48:23.277
I do not need the blanket...

599
00:48:26.781 --> 00:48:28.407
The Hand. Your Grace.

600
00:48:29.033 --> 00:48:32.036
- The King is resting.
- I will see him.

601
00:48:33.204 --> 00:48:34.413
Lean forward.

602
00:48:41.837 --> 00:48:44.673
I'm being endlessly fussed over. Lyonel.

603
00:48:45.382 --> 00:48:48.010
It's a wonder
I can visit the privy alone.

604
00:48:48.761 --> 00:48:49.762
Your Grace.

605
00:48:50.930 --> 00:48:52.973
What might this errand
be about. Lord Lyonel?

606
00:48:55.851 --> 00:48:57.186
Your Grace. I feel...

607
00:48:59.814 --> 00:49:02.399
I have come to resign my position
as Hand of the King.

608
00:49:04.026 --> 00:49:05.694
The episode in the yard this morning.

609
00:49:05.778 --> 00:49:08.823
My son Harwin has disgraced himself

610
00:49:08.906 --> 00:49:11.867
and every fishwife in King's Landing
will soon be telling the tale.

611
00:49:11.951 --> 00:49:16.122
Young Harwin's outburst was unfortunate.
it's true.

612
00:49:16.205 --> 00:49:17.915
But he's been expelled
from the City Watch.

613
00:49:17.998 --> 00:49:19.375
That seems punishment enough.

614
00:49:19.458 --> 00:49:21.043
Forgive me. Your Grace. it is not.

615
00:49:28.968 --> 00:49:33.139
You have served me
faithfully for many years.

616
00:49:33.222 --> 00:49:34.473
ten as Hand.

617
00:49:36.058 --> 00:49:40.229
Your advice has been sage.
unmarked by self-interest...

618
00:49:40.938 --> 00:49:43.691
which stands in contrast to all others.

619
00:49:44.984 --> 00:49:46.569
You speak kind words...

620
00:49:47.862 --> 00:49:49.864
but there is a shadow over my house

621
00:49:49.947 --> 00:49:52.158
and it grows ever darker.

622
00:49:52.241 --> 00:49:54.869
I can no longer serve you
with integrity.

623
00:49:56.287 --> 00:49:57.371
What is this shadow?

624
00:49:59.248 --> 00:50:01.625
Name it. if it casts such a gloom.

625
00:50:01.709 --> 00:50:06.338
Yes. we must have your reasoning
in plain language.

626
00:50:14.221 --> 00:50:15.222
I cannot.

627
00:50:17.474 --> 00:50:19.059
Then I cannot accept this.

628
00:50:19.143 --> 00:50:21.145
- My dear husband...
- I said no!

629
00:50:22.479 --> 00:50:25.107
- If you insist. my king.
- I do.

630
00:50:26.025 --> 00:50:28.068
You will continue in your service
to the Crown.

631
00:50:30.738 --> 00:50:32.781
I would then ask leave
to take my son from court

632
00:50:32.865 --> 00:50:35.951
and escort him back to the family seat
at Harrenhal.

633
00:50:36.035 --> 00:50:38.037
He is my heir

634
00:50:38.120 --> 00:50:39.914
and will be lord of Harren's castle
one day.

635
00:50:39.997 --> 00:50:42.625
It is time he assumed his duties there.

636
00:50:45.711 --> 00:50:46.795
Do it.

637
00:51:07.608 --> 00:51:09.610
Aren't you gonna help me?

638
00:51:49.066 --> 00:51:51.902
I took the liberty of beginning
without you. Your Grace.

639
00:51:51.986 --> 00:51:54.738
It seemed a sin to let
such a pie grow cold.

640
00:51:54.822 --> 00:51:57.700
You did wisely. Lord Larys.

641
00:51:57.783 --> 00:52:00.619
Though you had no such worry
about the wine. surely.

642
00:52:00.703 --> 00:52:03.330
Meat without wine is also a sin.

643
00:52:03.414 --> 00:52:04.665
Hmm.

644
00:52:08.961 --> 00:52:11.588
It's been my duty to tell you
of happenings about the castle.

645
00:52:11.672 --> 00:52:14.675
but tonight you know. and I do not.

646
00:52:15.551 --> 00:52:18.304
The King had an audience with my father.

647
00:52:18.387 --> 00:52:19.930
He attempted to resign his post.

648
00:52:21.015 --> 00:52:22.141
I thought as much.

649
00:52:23.600 --> 00:52:27.229
His honor's always been a millstone
about his esteemed neck.

650
00:52:29.398 --> 00:52:31.358
Interesting you said "attempted"?

651
00:52:31.442 --> 00:52:33.444
My lord husband refused to accept.

652
00:52:34.695 --> 00:52:38.657
Then he fell short of confessing
my brother's... transgressions.

653
00:52:38.741 --> 00:52:40.951
With his eruption in the yard.
your brother

654
00:52:41.035 --> 00:52:43.162
all but confessed the truth himself.

655
00:52:43.245 --> 00:52:45.456
Truth has many flavors. Your Grace.

656
00:52:46.540 --> 00:52:49.209
Do you expect the King to doom
his dear daughter to exile.

657
00:52:49.293 --> 00:52:51.128
or even...

658
00:52:52.713 --> 00:52:53.922
Talya. not now.

659
00:53:01.221 --> 00:53:04.808
It's a willful blindness. the King.

660
00:53:04.892 --> 00:53:06.619
I mean. you'd surely
suffer the same affliction.

661
00:53:06.643 --> 00:53:08.562
- if it came to it.
- I would not.

662
00:53:10.397 --> 00:53:13.275
Lord Lyonel is to escort
Ser Harwin back to Harrenhal

663
00:53:13.359 --> 00:53:16.779
to watch over his seat
whilst he continues to serve as Hand.

664
00:53:17.363 --> 00:53:22.076
But the Hand is compromised
by the acts of his son.

665
00:53:22.159 --> 00:53:27.122
My father cannot give
unbiased counsel to the King.

666
00:53:27.206 --> 00:53:30.501
It is now that I most rue
the absence of my own father.

667
00:53:30.584 --> 00:53:32.520
He wouldn't hesitate
to speak the truth to the King.

668
00:53:32.544 --> 00:53:34.088
If Otto Hightower were still Hand...

669
00:53:34.171 --> 00:53:36.590
You cannot say. my queen.
that your father would be

670
00:53:36.673 --> 00:53:38.217
impartial in this matter.

671
00:53:38.300 --> 00:53:40.511
No. but he would be partial to me!

672
00:53:49.937 --> 00:53:52.940
In all of King's Landing.
is there no one to take my side?

673
00:54:19.091 --> 00:54:22.302
What a collection of heroes
I have before me.

674
00:54:26.265 --> 00:54:28.016
A murderer...

675
00:54:28.600 --> 00:54:30.686
a deviant...

676
00:54:31.186 --> 00:54:33.188
a traitor to the Crown.

677
00:54:33.897 --> 00:54:38.110
For your crimes. you've been sentenced
to death by hanging.

678
00:54:40.028 --> 00:54:42.030
What do you want with us?

679
00:54:45.200 --> 00:54:48.203
I am prepared to offer you mercy...

680
00:54:49.830 --> 00:54:52.833
<i>if you're prepared
to pay a little price.</i>

681
00:55:16.940 --> 00:55:18.668
<i>Push. my lady.</i>

682
00:55:18.692 --> 00:55:21.278
<i>Push! Push!</i>

683
00:55:22.154 --> 00:55:23.322
Push!

684
00:55:23.405 --> 00:55:25.949
- You must push!
- Push!

685
00:55:27.910 --> 00:55:30.162
It needs to come now!

686
00:55:30.245 --> 00:55:31.455
Push!

687
00:55:33.499 --> 00:55:35.125
Push!

688
00:55:35.834 --> 00:55:38.003
You must push now. my lady!

689
00:55:39.087 --> 00:55:40.507
Push!

690
00:55:58.857 --> 00:56:00.859
I've reached the limit of my art.

691
00:56:02.736 --> 00:56:04.363
The child will not come.

692
00:56:07.115 --> 00:56:09.117
Ah. my brave girl.

693
00:56:14.581 --> 00:56:16.061
I am very sorry. my prince.

694
00:56:17.960 --> 00:56:19.962
We could lay open the womb...

695
00:56:20.963 --> 00:56:23.173
try to remove the infant

696
00:56:23.257 --> 00:56:24.883
by way of the blade.

697
00:56:26.134 --> 00:56:29.179
But I cannot say
for a surety whether it lives.

698
00:56:29.263 --> 00:56:30.722
Would the mother survive it?

699
00:56:33.058 --> 00:56:34.059
No.

700
00:57:05.048 --> 00:57:07.259
Vhagar. <i>dracarys.</i>

701
00:57:12.598 --> 00:57:13.765
<i>Dracarys!</i>

702
00:57:16.435 --> 00:57:17.853
<i>Dracarys!</i>

703
00:57:22.441 --> 00:57:24.026
<i>Dracarys.</i>

704
00:57:24.818 --> 00:57:26.820
<i>Dracarys!</i>

705
00:57:28.947 --> 00:57:30.532
<i>Dracarys.</i>

706
00:57:51.094 --> 00:57:52.304
Laena!

707
00:58:15.243 --> 00:58:17.163
Be good to your mother. lads.

708
00:58:17.496 --> 00:58:19.122
I'll visit when I can.

709
00:58:22.584 --> 00:58:24.044
But that may be some time.

710
00:58:27.923 --> 00:58:28.924
Jace.

711
00:58:35.972 --> 00:58:37.391
I will return...

712
00:58:40.060 --> 00:58:41.478
I promise.

713
00:58:56.326 --> 00:59:00.288
I will be a stranger when we meet again.

714
00:59:17.180 --> 00:59:18.181
Princess.

715
00:59:40.579 --> 00:59:43.290
We will exchange letters by raven.

716
00:59:43.373 --> 00:59:47.002
- Won't that be fun?
- Is Harwin Strong my father?

717
00:59:51.173 --> 00:59:52.549
Am I a bastard?

718
00:59:57.387 --> 00:59:58.930
You are a Targaryen.

719
01:00:00.932 --> 01:00:02.100
That's all that matters.

720
01:00:27.042 --> 01:00:28.084
A word?

721
01:00:35.091 --> 01:00:36.426
I take it he's gone.

722
01:00:39.012 --> 01:00:40.722
We're finished here. We're leaving.

723
01:00:43.725 --> 01:00:46.603
What of your offer? Jace and Helaena?

724
01:00:46.686 --> 01:00:48.438
I have been undermined...

725
01:00:49.314 --> 01:00:52.526
and made a spectacle.
They whisper about me in the corridors.

726
01:00:52.609 --> 01:00:54.986
Well. I leave them to it.

727
01:00:58.949 --> 01:01:00.116
To Dragonstone then?

728
01:01:01.159 --> 01:01:02.410
We should've left years ago.

729
01:01:08.667 --> 01:01:10.460
What of your position?

730
01:01:10.544 --> 01:01:12.879
You've always said
if you were absent from court.

731
01:01:12.963 --> 01:01:15.882
she would pour her honey
in your father's ear.

732
01:01:16.550 --> 01:01:19.719
The wise sailor
flees the storm as it gathers.

733
01:01:21.972 --> 01:01:23.390
Laenor...

734
01:01:25.141 --> 01:01:26.393
bring him.

735
01:01:28.186 --> 01:01:30.313
We'll need every sword we can muster.

736
01:02:46.848 --> 01:02:50.268
Fire! I will burn!

737
01:02:50.352 --> 01:02:53.063
Harwin! Harwin!

738
01:03:17.504 --> 01:03:21.132
<i>What are children.
but a weakness?</i>

739
01:03:24.678 --> 01:03:26.304
<i>A folly?</i>

740
01:03:27.472 --> 01:03:29.307
<i>A futility?</i>

741
01:03:34.521 --> 01:03:36.690
<i>Through them. you imagine you cheat</i>

742
01:03:36.773 --> 01:03:39.985
<i>the great darkness of its victory.</i>

743
01:03:55.125 --> 01:04:00.130
<i>You will persist forever.
in some form or another.</i>

744
01:04:02.924 --> 01:04:06.094
<i>As if they will keep you
from the dust.</i>

745
01:04:17.147 --> 01:04:21.818
<i>But for them.
you surrender what you should not.</i>

746
01:04:24.612 --> 01:04:28.408
<i>You may know what is
the right thing to be done.</i>

747
01:04:28.491 --> 01:04:31.870
<i>but love stays the hand.</i>

748
01:04:40.795 --> 01:04:42.005
<i>Love...</i>

749
01:04:44.132 --> 01:04:46.134
<i>is a downfall.</i>

750
01:04:51.097 --> 01:04:54.601
Best to make your way
through life unencumbered...

751
01:04:56.186 --> 01:04:57.645
if you ask me.

752
01:05:01.316 --> 01:05:02.609
They're dead.

753
01:05:02.692 --> 01:05:05.695
You've heard the stories
of Harrenhal. Your Grace.

754
01:05:07.405 --> 01:05:09.449
It was built in hubris
by Harren the Black

755
01:05:09.532 --> 01:05:11.910
as a monument to his own greatness.

756
01:05:11.993 --> 01:05:14.996
Blood mixed into the mortar.

757
01:05:17.165 --> 01:05:19.626
It is said to be a cursed place.

758
01:05:20.293 --> 01:05:24.089
That it passes judgment
on all who pass beneath its gates.

759
01:05:24.172 --> 01:05:25.799
You...

760
01:05:25.882 --> 01:05:27.884
You passed judgment.

761
01:05:29.511 --> 01:05:30.887
The Queen makes a wish.

762
01:05:32.806 --> 01:05:36.476
What servant of the realm
would not strive to fulfill it?

763
01:05:38.436 --> 01:05:42.065
I assume you will write
to your father now?

764
01:05:44.025 --> 01:05:45.026
Larys...

765
01:05:46.194 --> 01:05:48.446
I did not wish for this.

766
01:05:50.657 --> 01:05:54.536
I feel certain you will reward me...

767
01:05:56.329 --> 01:05:58.665
when the time is right.

767
01:05:59.305 --> 01:06:59.925
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
